 Keep illustrates the harsh consequences of excessive sentences and demonstrates a keen need to reconsider punishment policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aPrisonersxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aamerican prisoners.  achallenges.  acrafting lives of notable purpose.  adying in prison.  aeventual decline.  aexcessive sentences.  agrowing population.  aharsh consequences.  ainmates.  ainstitutions.  ajail.  alife in prison.  alife without parole.  alifers.  aneglected.  aprison staff.  aprison.  areconsider punishment policy.  aserving life sentences.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520971875zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520971875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520971875.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  